tourBios.exmtStatus: Fully Exempt / 28th Web.com Tour Qualifier at the 2011 PGA TOUR Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.curYearHigh: Had a hole-in-one during the third round of the Cox Classic. Aced the 229-yard 16th hole with a 5-iron for his sixth career hole-in-one. It was his first in competition.
tourBios.carHigh: 2008: Only previous TOUR experience was a missed cut at the Buick Open.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: His Grosse Ile High School team won two state championships...Won the 2004 Michigan State Amateur.
tourBios.personal: Brother Steven played golf at Michigan State...Instructors include Jerry Pasco, Jim Yuhas and Eden Foster...Played on Hooters Tour (2004-2008) and Canadian Tour (2009-2011)...Favorite course he has played is Calusa Pines GC in Naples, FL...Never travels without his headphones...Superstition is teeing the ball up the same way every hole...Top websites are espn.com and jackthreads.com...Favorite college teams are the Michigan Wolverines and the Michigan State Spartans. Follows all Detroit professional teams...Went to high school with and played baseball with Texas Rangers outfielder Josh Hamilton...Favorite TV show is "How I Met Your Mother" and his top movies are "Happy Gilmore" and "Days of Thunder." Favorite group is the Dave Matthews Band. Enjoys sushi and Mexican food. Favorite athletes to watch are LeBron James and Tiger Woods. Favorite cities to visit are Chicago, Detroit and Scottsdale, while his top vacation spot is Boyne Mountain in Gaylord, Mich...Favorite gadgets are his cell phone and iPad. Favorite apps are Facebook and Golf Channel...Carries almonds, Clif Bars and an Amore Mio-Snack-Bar in his golf bag...Has special Rocket Tour headcovers...Dream foursome includes Woods, Matthews and Kevin James...Bucket list includes playing on the PGA TOUR and traveling the world...Favorite quote is "Anyone can beat anyone on any given day."

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour in 2012 is T29th at the BMW Charity Pro-Am presented by SYNNEX Corporation.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks T94th in Heat Index(Finish)-last 6 evts on the Web.com Tour.
